<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="294" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1437]" pageId="2" pageNumber="294">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1124,1149]" pageId="2" pageNumber="294">Remarks.</emphasis>
By the prothoracic shape, and pubescence pattern of the body, 
<taxonomicName authority="Nascimento &amp; Heffern, 2018" authorityName="Nascimento &amp; Heffern" authorityYear="2018" box="[1040,1309,1124,1148]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Leptostylus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obrienorum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1040,1309,1124,1148]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="294">Leptostylus obrienorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1317,1409,1124,1149]" pageId="2" pageNumber="294" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1317,1409,1124,1149]" pageId="2" pageNumber="294">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Fisher, 1942" authorityName="Fisher" authorityYear="1942" box="[270,629,1159,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Leptostylus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bruesi">
<emphasis box="[270,477,1160,1184]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="294">Leptostylus bruesi</emphasis>
Fisher, 1942
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[648,760,1159,1184]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8. 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1925,1948]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,195,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[195,1393,195,1888]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. 1–4, Leptostylus obrienorum sp. nov., holotype, male: 1, dorsal view; 2, ventral view; 3, lateral view; 4, frontal view. 5–8, Leptostylus bruesi Fisher, 1942, holotype female (photos taken from: http://insects.oeb.harvard.edu/mcz/): 5, dorsal view; 6, lateral view; 7, frontal view; 8, labels." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444191/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="294">Figs. 5–8</figureCitation>
). The new species differs by the small and convex central tubercle of the pronotum, absence of conical tubercles on dorsal area of the posterior half of the elytra, smaller triangular area of the posterior quarter of the elytra, and posterior fifth of the elytra concolorous to the remaining areas of the elytra. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fisher" authorityYear="1942" box="[396,497,1268,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Leptostylus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bruesi">
<emphasis box="[396,497,1268,1292]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="294">L. bruesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the central tubercle of pronotum is elevated and conical (
<figureCitation box="[1151,1220,1268,1293]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8. 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1925,1948]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,195,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[195,1393,195,1888]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. 1–4, Leptostylus obrienorum sp. nov., holotype, male: 1, dorsal view; 2, ventral view; 3, lateral view; 4, frontal view. 5–8, Leptostylus bruesi Fisher, 1942, holotype female (photos taken from: http://insects.oeb.harvard.edu/mcz/): 5, dorsal view; 6, lateral view; 7, frontal view; 8, labels." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444191/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="294">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), the dorsal area of the posterior half of the elytra have conical tubercles (spine-shaped) throughout (
<figureCitation box="[1081,1150,1303,1328]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8. 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1925,1948]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,195,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[195,1393,195,1888]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. 1–4, Leptostylus obrienorum sp. nov., holotype, male: 1, dorsal view; 2, ventral view; 3, lateral view; 4, frontal view. 5–8, Leptostylus bruesi Fisher, 1942, holotype female (photos taken from: http://insects.oeb.harvard.edu/mcz/): 5, dorsal view; 6, lateral view; 7, frontal view; 8, labels." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444191/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="294">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), the posterior triangular area of the elytra occupies almost the entire posterior quarter and the posterior fifth is clearer than the remaining areas (
<figureCitation box="[230,305,1375,1400]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8. 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1925,1948]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,195,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[195,1393,195,1888]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. 1–4, Leptostylus obrienorum sp. nov., holotype, male: 1, dorsal view; 2, ventral view; 3, lateral view; 4, frontal view. 5–8, Leptostylus bruesi Fisher, 1942, holotype female (photos taken from: http://insects.oeb.harvard.edu/mcz/): 5, dorsal view; 6, lateral view; 7, frontal view; 8, labels." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444191/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="294">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). In addition to the morphological differences, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fisher" authorityYear="1942" box="[878,985,1376,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Leptostylus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bruesi">
<emphasis box="[878,985,1376,1400]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="294">L. bruesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is registered only for 
<collectingCountry box="[1263,1356,1375,1400]" name="Jamaica" pageId="2" pageNumber="294">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
, while 
<taxonomicName authority="Nascimento &amp; Heffern, 2018" authorityName="Nascimento &amp; Heffern" authorityYear="2018" box="[151,417,1412,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Leptostylus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obrienorum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,417,1412,1436]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="294">Leptostylus obrienorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[424,514,1412,1437]" pageId="2" pageNumber="294" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[424,514,1412,1437]" pageId="2" pageNumber="294">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is from 
<collectingCountry box="[608,676,1412,1437]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="294">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[691,807,1412,1437]" country="Brazil" name="Rondonia" pageId="2" pageNumber="294">Rondônia</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
